s, Brigham convincingly reveals, is pervasive precisely because political life finds its expression in a surprising variety of legal forms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aCivil rightszUnited States. 0aJurisprudencezUnited States. 0aLawxPolitical aspects. 0aLawzUnited StatesxPhilosophy. 0aLawzUnited States. 0aSex and lawzUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814723494423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814723494.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK